          <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">phylogeny</ENAMEX>. Sequences most likely to be misrepresented in
          the ancestor by this reconstruction are phage <ENAMEX TYPE="SUBSTANCE">genes</ENAMEX> or
          insertion elements, which may move in and out of genomes
          too frequently for ancestral <ENAMEX TYPE="GPE_DESC">states</ENAMEX> to be reconstructed
          using parsimony. 
          <ENAMEX TYPE="ORG_DESC">Buchnera</ENAMEX> lacks phage or insertion
          <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">sequences</ENAMEX> [ <ENAMEX TYPE="LAW">8</ENAMEX>].
